gomodel:SYNGO_4752  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6C: in NCAM-/-, which disrupts AP2-based SV endocytosis, pulldowns of synaptophysin from crude SV fractions yielded a strong increase in AP-3. This suggests an increase of endocytosis via AP3 pathways.\n\nFigure 7. AP3-mediated bulk membrane retrieval was enhanced in NCAM-/- synaptic boutons.\n\nFigure 8. AP3-dependent synaptic vesicle endocytosis and intrasynaptic processing are upregulated in NCAM-/- synaptic boutons.\n\nThe antibody for AP3 targeted AP3B2.. Experimental description: M&M: \"To prepare cultures of hippocampal neurons, 1- to 3-d-old C57BL/6J and NCAM-/- mice of either sex from homozygous breeding pairs were used.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"neuronal adaptin-like protein beta (βNAP) subunit of AP-3 (clone 18, catalog #610892)\"\nnote; this is AP3B2" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-04" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4752" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

